<title>UK: British Steel to build facility in India.</title>
<headline>British Steel to build facility in India.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-11-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>British Steel Plc said on Monday that it agreed with Jindal Iron &amp; Steel Co. Ltd to build organic coating line and roll profiling facilities in India at a cost of 29 million stg.  </p>
<p>British Steel said this was its first venture in this geographical location.</p>
<p>It said in a statement that whilst the venture was relatively modest at this stage it believed it signalled the start of a &quot;new and significant phase in the company's development.&quot;</p>
